<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1290,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">
The species under consideration belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[640,787,1291,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Microscapha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[640,787,1291,1315]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">Microscapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the combination of the following characters: (
<number box="[1414,1426,1291,1315]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="1.0">1</number>
) well developed, small, triangular scutellum, (
<number box="[667,682,1327,1351]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
) antennae short, with 
<number box="[939,951,1326,1351]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="3.0">3</number>
-segmented club, (
<number box="[1165,1179,1327,1351]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="3.0">3</number>
) antennomere 
<number box="[1351,1365,1327,1351]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="3.0">3</number>
much shorter and narrower than antennomere 
<number box="[645,661,1363,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="2.0">2</number>
, (
<number box="[691,706,1363,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="4.0">4</number>
) pronotal posterior margin bisinuate, (
<number box="[1185,1199,1362,1387]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="5.0">5</number>
) pronotum without depression, (
<number box="[297,312,1398,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="6.0">6</number>
) metasternum with median longitudinal depression, (
<number box="[929,944,1399,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="7.0">7</number>
) metacoxae large, (
<number box="[1174,1188,1399,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="8.0">8</number>
) metatibiae with two long serrate spurs, (
<number box="[371,386,1435,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" value="9.0">9</number>
) sutural stria well-developed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
